    "content_hash": "56f369654b4c3316",
    "department": "GTM",
    "description": "Replit is the agentic software creation platform that enables anyone to build applications using natural language. With millions of users worldwide, Replit is democratizing software development by removing traditional barriers to application creation.\n\n\nWe're looking for a Startups Partnerships Lead to build and scale Replit's presence in the startup and SMB ecosystem. This is a high-impact, externally-facing role at the intersection of business development, community building, and product evangelism. You'll own the strategy for how Replit shows up for early-stage founders, startup studios, incubators, and accelerators and you'll close the partnerships that drive growth.\n\nThis role is ideal for someone who has lived the startup world, understands founder psychology, and knows how to build trust quickly with technical and non-technical builders alike.\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Own the end-to-end partnership lifecycle for startups and SMBs, from prospecting and outreach to negotiation, close, and ongoing relationship management\n\n - Build and manage a portfolio of partnerships with accelerators, incubators, venture studios, and startup communities (YC, Techstars, On Deck, and similar)\n\n - Develop co-marketing and co-selling motions with ecosystem partners to drive Replit adoption among early-stage founders\n\n - Work closely with Product and Growth to surface startup-specific use cases and champion features that serve builders\n\n - Represent Replit at startup events, demo days, and founder communities — online and in-person\n\n - Design and execute programs that give startups meaningful access to Replit credits, tools, and community\n\n - Track and report on partnership performance metrics, ensuring relationships convert to measurable business impact\n\n - Collaborate with the broader Partnerships team on cross-functional initiatives across education, enterprise, and international expansion\n\n\n\nREQUIRED SKILLS \u0026 EXPERIENCE\n\n - 8+ years of experience in partnerships, business development, or sales, ideally in a startup or high-growth tech environment\n\n - Deep familiarity with the startup ecosystem: accelerators, angel networks, VC firms, and the communities where founders spend time\n\n - Proven ability to source, structure, and close strategic partnerships, not just manage them\n\n - Strong communicator who can adapt messaging for technical founders, non-technical operators, and institutional partners alike\n\n - Self-starter with a bias for action; comfortable with ambiguity and excited to build programs from scratch\n\n - Data-driven mindset, you measure what matters and use insights to iterate quickly\n\n - Genuine passion for the future of software creation and democratizing access to developer tools\n\n\n\nBONUS QUALIFICATIONS\n\n - Experience as a founder, or working directly inside an accelerator or VC firm\n\n - Background in developer tools, coding education, or SaaS platforms\n\n - Existing relationships in the startup ecosystem you'd bring to the role\n\n - Experience building or managing partner programs at scale\n\nThis is a full-time role that can be held from our Foster City, CA office. The role has an in-office requirement of Monday, Wednesday, and Friday.\n\nFull-Time Employee Benefits Include:\n\n💰 Competitive Salary \u0026 Equity\n\n💹 401(k) Program with a 4% match\n\n⚕️ Health, Dental, Vision and Life Insurance\n\n🩼 Short Term and Long Term Disability\n\n🚼 Paid Parental, Medical, Caregiver Leave\n\n🚗 Commuter Benefits\n\n📱 Monthly Wellness Stipend\n\n🧑‍💻 Autonomous Work Environment\n\n🖥 In Office Set-Up Reimbursement\n\n🏝 Flexible Time Off (FTO) + Holidays\n\n🚀 Quarterly Team Gatherings\n\n☕ In Office Amenities\n\nWant to learn more about what we are up to?\n\n - Meet the Replit Agent https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IYiVPrxY8-Y\n\n - Replit: Make an app for that https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4zd9hzngFwY\n\n - Replit Blog https://blog.replit.com/\n\n - Amjad TED Talk https://youtu.be/kCudFI4tcpg?si=l4ViCejV_f2RZkDi\n\nInterviewing + Culture at Replit\n\n - Operating Principles https://blog.replit.com/operating-principles\n\n - Reasons not to work at Replit https://blog.replit.com/reasons-not-to-join-replit\n\nTo achieve our mission of making programming more accessible around the world, we need our team to be representative of the world. We welcome your unique perspective and experiences in shaping this product. We encourage people from all kinds of backgrounds to apply, including and especially candidates from underrepresented and non-traditional backgrounds.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
